{"id": 38097, "title": "Hatachi no Ryouma with Kurofune-kun!", "synopsis": "A Shinagawa ward tourism anime. The anime was made in honor of the 150th anniversary of the Meiji Restoration.\n \nIt stars Sakamoto Ryouma, a historical figure who took part in overthrowing the Tokugawa shogunate. He spent most of his youth in Shinagawa under the Tosa Clan residence and a statue of him was erected in his honor. He's considered a hero of Edo and worked as a cost guard/battery staff when Commodore Perry landed in Japan with black ships.\n\nHere, the anime has a young Ryouma encounter Kurofune-kun, a black ship chibi mascot, as they time slip to modern Shinagawa. Kurofune-kun shows him the sights and they meet other historical figures who time slipped. ", "genres": [{"id": 13, "name": "Historical"}, {"id": 15, "name": "Kids"}, {"id": 24, "name": "Sci-Fi"}]}